x = np.arange(0, np.pi*2, 0.05)
y = np.sin(x)

fig, ax = plt.subplots()
ax.plot(x,y)
plt.title(' ')
fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize = [6,4],dpi = 72*2)
ax.plot(x,y)
plt.title(' dpi')

ax.plot(x,y)
plt.title('   dpi');

ax.plot(x,y)
plt.title('figsize=(6,3), dpi=200');

In [19]:
#             
# ,  ,    .    
x = np.arange(0, np.pi*2, 0.05)
y1 = np.sin(x)
y2 = np.sin(2*x)
y3 = np.sin(3*x)
fig, ax = plt.subplots()
ax.plot(x,y1,'ys-') #   (y),    (s),   (-)
ax.plot(x,y2,'go--') #   (g),    (o),   (--)
ax.plot(x,y3,'k:')  #   (g),  ,  ,    (:)
#  : labels -    ,       
# loc -  
ax.legend(labels = ('x', '2x','3x'), loc = 'lower left');
In [20]:
#     
x = np.zeros(8)

fig, ax = plt.subplots()

# RGB:
ax.plot(x, color = (0.9, 0.2, 0.9))

# RGBA (  0.5):
ax.plot(np.arange(-1, 7),
        color = (0.1, 0.2, 0.9, 0.5),
        linewidth = 12)

# hex RGB:
ax.plot(x + 1, color = '#ff0000') # 

# hex RGBA:
ax.plot(x + 2, color = '#ff00003a') #  

#     [0, 1]:
ax.plot(x + 3, color = '0.3')

#    {'b', 'g', 'r', 'c', 'm', 'y', 'k', 'w'}:
ax.plot(x + 4, color = 'g')

#    X11/CSS4:
ax.plot(x + 5, color = 'indigo')

fig.set_facecolor('mintcream') #     (   X11/CSS4)
ax.set_facecolor('whitesmoke') #     (   X11/CSS4)
In [21]:
#        ,    plot  label
x = np.arange(0, np.pi*2, 0.05)
y1 = np.sin(x)
y2 = np.sin(2*x)
y3 = np.sin(3*x)
fig, ax = plt.subplots()
ax.plot(x,y1,'ys-',label = 'x')
ax.plot(x,y2,'go--',label = '2x')
ax.plot(x,y3,'k:',label = '3x')
ax.legend(loc = 'lower left');
